        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 9. Porcellidium fimbriatum Claus, 1863. Female: (A) adult showing colour pattern; (C) caudal rami (left dorsal, right ventral); (D) detail of caudal ramus; (E, H) genital double-somite, detail of posterior lobe; (G) genital opening. Male: (B) adult; (F) caudal ramus. Drawings of specimens from Scotland. Scale bar: A, B = 0.45 mm. C = 0.13 mm. D, E, F, G = 0.08 mm. H = 0.23 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4684641/files/figure.png" .

